reviews_data.review_text:
Best Greek food in Cape Town.
The Mezze is always so delicious and tastes exactly as it would in Greece. A must try restaurant. Wonderful variety and everything flavourful and delicious.

We ordered the classic greek yiro - It could have been better served. The tzatziki sauce had way too many onions and overpowered the beef filling. The pita was much thicker than the traditional making the folded gyro quite messy. I would suggest the souvlakia as a better choice.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for the constructive feedback

reviews_data.review_text: Delicious food but very poor service. From the moment we were seated, my family and I had to try to get a waiter's attention so that they could take our drink order. After we got our drinks, we took two to three minutes to decide what to order, and we sat for a long time without any waiters checking to see if we were ready to order. We then got the waiter's attention once more and placed our meal orders, which was the last time we saw our waiter or any waiters at our table. Whenever we needed something, we had to try and get the waiter's attention. The food was delicious, but the service was poor.
Delicious food! Flavors are all there! Will definitely go back again.

Sad to see an establishment going down the drain so quickly. Restaurant grubby, toilets dreadful and food average to poor. We had lamb kleftiko ( their flagship dish) reheated and with oversalted gravy. Won't be back.

If you need authentic Greek food then mykonos is the place
#MYKONOS SEA POINT
#THE ORIGINAL

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Calamari, Hummus, Lamb Shank, Meze Platter, Baklava

reviews_data.review_text: Good decent Greek style food. Fresh and well prepared. Friendly staff. I will come back :)

Best service and good food l loved the Seafood trio was made with love and served warm and the prawns were delicious, tasty and fresh

Definitely coming back and recommending a friend  to tell a friend

The service at the restaurant was good they were able to accommodate an ever growing group of my dining companions. The ambience of the restaurant was good as well.

The felt the veg options on the menu to be a bit limited though I was pleasantly surprised that the veg moussaka came with an additional side, and opted for the chips.

The moussaka was hearty and filled me up like a home cooked meal, but was also served with some parmesan on the side which gave it a touch more flavour.
Always good, good food and good service

Leckere Lamb Chops, schön gegrillt, gut gewürzt. Dazu eine gute Flasche Rotwein, sehr schmackhaft! Service schnell und auf Zack.
Das Ambiente ist entsprechend mau, direkt an der Straße, laute Autos, häufig Polizei Sirene.
Good food, almost like in Greece , but I will be back 🫡

We chose Mykonos Taverna to celebrate our 3rd wedding anniversary, and it turned out to be one of the most joyful and memorable evenings we’ve ever had. From the moment we walked in, we were welcomed with warmth and genuine hospitality that immediately set the tone for the night.

The atmosphere was vibrant yet intimate, with a cozy charm that made us feel both at home and transported to Greece at the same time. The décor, the music, and the energy of the place created such a festive backdrop for our special occasion.

The food was nothing short of amazing. Every dish was prepared with care and bursting with flavor — from the starters to the mains, everything felt authentic and fresh. The prawns were perfectly cooked, the lamb tender and full of depth, and the mezze plates were a delightful way to share and savor together. Each bite reminded us why Mykonos Taverna is such a gem.

The service truly elevated the evening. The staff were attentive without being intrusive, and they seemed genuinely invested in making our anniversary feel special. Small touches — like checking in at just the right moments, ensuring our glasses were never empty, and celebrating with us through kind words — made us feel cared for in a way that went beyond the ordinary.

What stood out most was how everything came together seamlessly: the food, the atmosphere, the service, and the sense of celebration. It wasn’t just dinner; it was an experience that honored our milestone and left us with beautiful memories.

Thank you, Mykonos Taverna, for making our 3rd anniversary so unforgettable. We left with full hearts, grateful smiles, and the certainty that we’ll be back again to celebrate many more moments in the future.
The vibe is amazing, the food is spectacular!!!Very cheerful atmosphere.

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Kleftiko Lamb, Lamb Skewers Spanakopita and Fries with Tzatziki

reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much for positive feedback and thank you so much for your support

reviews_data.review_text:
Tapas was good
Baby chicken tough and not cooked properly, mentioned to management,
response disappointing.
Toilet facilities need serious attention ( missing tiles etc, not clean)
Generally tatty and scruffy, won’t go back

We just got notified that our order was cancelled after calling 6 times speaking to a manager once who said he would send it off right away. The last few calls the phone was picked up and hung up.
We placed our order at 19:30 and its now 21:30, had to make a plan to feed the kids.
Turned my favourite Greek spot into a future NO GO.

I took my mom for her birthday and had a very disappointing experience. I was told on the phone that only a set menu was available, yet when we arrived, other tables were allowed to order from the regular menu and received much faster service. We waited extremely long for both the starter and main with no communication from staff. As the only table of people of colour, we also received noticeably less attention and smaller portions compared to other tables. It felt unfair and unwelcoming, and I wouldn’t return.

EDIT – Response to the owner:

Your reply is disappointing and avoids the actual issue. I don’t understand what the race of your staff has to do with the service my table received. At no point did I blame your staff or mention that as part of the problem.

My review was about the service we experienced — the lack of communication, the inconsistency on the menu, the delays, the smaller portions, and the fact that every table around us received noticeably better attention.

Are you suggesting I imagined being ignored while other tables were being checked on?

Instead of addressing anything I actually raised, you deflected. I expected accountability, not dismissal.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Im sorry you feel that way and whatever you experienced as it was def not done deliberately. With regards to " people of colour" i think we are way past that point in this current world.
Dont know if you were aware but 100% of my staff are of colour.

reviews_data.review_text: I wish I could comment on the food but we have been waiting for our order for 1.5 hours via Uber Eats. 3 drivers have given up and have been told that the food is 'almost ready' each time I have called. I am struggling to understand why Mykonos is on Uber Eats at all?!

Disappointed. My family has been coming here for years and has always had excellent food and service. Now that the restaurant has relaunched in the new space the focus seems to be more on appearance than food. My lamb chops were ok, though the portion size is definitely smaller now, especially if you make the mistake of ordering a side salad, which is now served in the tiniest of bowls. Another in our party ordered the moussaka, which came cold. On closer inspection the meat was raw. Then the grilled chicken was also undercooked and still very pink inside. Our grumpy waiter also poured a different wine into our glasses before we emptied the first one, creating a rather unpleasant blend. That in spite of the very hefty corkage they now charge if you want to bring your own special bottle. This kind of quality might fly while Cape Town is in its busy year-end season, but those of us who live up the road have too many excellent fwood choices to make the same mistakes twice. Please fix your restaurant Mykonos! We love the way you used to be.

reviews_data.review_text: Tasty Greek food , not expensive, great atmosphere and good service!

We recently held the after party for our Daughters Baptism. Our guests cannot stop singing Mykonos’ praises.

Thank you Dimitri for an absolute memorable evening in the new restaurant. May you continue to grow from strength to strength…

We came here for dinner as it was the closest place to where we were staying and we had just arrived. When we arrived we were wowed by how lovely it looked inside and the atmosphere. The staff were incredibly friendly to us and there was nothing they wouldn’t do for us! When the food arrived we all said everything we had was absolutely delicious Stretch (the manager looked after us most of the night and he was so friendly and chatty. Bond also looked after us and made sure we had everything we needed all the time! We will definitely be back again!

Just celebrated a 80th Birthday at Mykonos.

Only to have it dampened by a lady complaining of the repeated Birthday songs celebrated by 3 separate patrons.
The owner did not brush you off you would just not accept his explanation.

The owner was threatened by Alex with a google review which she wrote at her table.What a bully to spoil the Birthday of an 80 year old.

You were warned! This a Greek restaurant where they break plates and celebrate.

There was no karaoke merely the daughter singing Happy Birthday to her Mother who is 80 followed by a speech from her son and grandson which was no more than 10 minutes.Alex don't come back and don't let the door hit you on the way out your family must have been embarrassed at the scene you made.

Seriously? LOL... I find that review by Alex Elliot ridiculously uncalled for.
People celebrate birthdays & life everywhere,  they do not need your permission to celebrate the gift of life ( especially when its an 80th birthday in a GREEK RESTAURANT) maybe next time if you don't want a beautiful atmosphere filled with love and togetherness,  consider having lunch in the park or in your own kitchen.
Thank you Dimitri and Mykonos team for yet another spectacular celebration....its exactly what a Greek restaurant is intended for.

We shared the most beautiful day celebrating an intimate 80th birthday today. There were three birthdays of patrons at the same time and the atmosphere was juts incredible. The food, the service the energy was just wonderful! Thank you

We recently had lunch at Mykonos to celebrate a very special occasion: the owner’s mother’s 80th birthday. The atmosphere was warm, joyful, and full of life, exactly what you would hope for when marking such an important milestone.

Unfortunately, a table next to us complained loudly about the noise and even about a short speech that was made in honor of the birthday. It was disappointing to witness such a lack of empathy. Celebrations are part of what makes restaurants lively and human, and moments like this should be appreciated, not criticized.

Despite this, the staff handled the situation professionally, and the afternoon remained memorable. Mykonos is a wonderful place for good food, great hospitality, and meaningful moments. Some people would probably be happier staying at home if they cannot appreciate others’ joy, but for us, it was a beautiful lunch.

Didn't warn us of a birthday party with speakers. Very loud and repeated renditions of Happy birthday song and terrible karaoke at maximum volume. Owner did not care when we complained about the noise. Will not return.

The food looked and smelled sooo divine I forgot to take photos! That just means I NEED TO GO BACK!!

We went late at night and it was lovely. If it is your birthday they sing for you (yay!). No playes were broken though. It is a family restaurant which feels warm and looks authentic.

We ordered 3 meals and shared among ourselves to taste everything. We had the lamb chops (so juicy and succulent); the chicken fillet with feta and parmesan (rich, creamy and delightful) and we had the seafood trio (thinking about the fish makes me want to have it all over again. The highlight was the kingklip; the calamari was great to but the prawns were just above average). I would rate the food an 8.5 out of 10. They also have homemade chilli (bonus!)

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Chicken and Chips, Fish and Chips, Chicken Melintzane

reviews_data.review_text: We went once, food average, nothing to rave about. Service was OK
Service, atmosphere as though you were in Greece.  The messe platter was divine.

Three of of three dishes were really sub par… tough meat and dry fish.
Very loud and bad acoustics so you can’t hear the person across from you easily.
Won’t be returning soon

Despite many positive reviews, my main issue lies not with the service, but with the food itself. Having had high hopes for this place, especially as a lamb enthusiast, I was thrilled to see kleftiko(lamb shank)—one of my favorite Greek dishes—on the menu. However, my excitement quickly turned to disappointment. This was, without a doubt, the worst kleftiko I've ever tasted. The meat was as dry as cardboard, burnt to a crisp on one side, completely devoid of any flavor, and to make matters worse, it was the most expensive item on the menu.

When I voiced my concerns about the dryness of the dish, the person who appeared to be the manager or owner, sitting at the cash register, seemed entirely indifferent. He didn't even bother to offer an apology or any form of acknowledgment. This lack of concern for customer satisfaction only added to my disappointment.

Overall, my experience was profoundly underwhelming, and I will certainly not be returning to Mykonos. It’s disheartening when a place with such potential falls short, both in terms of food quality and customer care.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hi Dylan 
Thank you for your constructive  criticism

reviews_data.review_text: Very nice place
Délicieux, les plats sont copieux et savoureux, le service est rapide et attentionnés, nous avons pris la salade grecque, les dolmades, des brochettes et des aubergines et tout était très bon !
Gezellige plek. Overdekt buitenterras met heaters. Zeer vriendelijk personeel en uitstekend eten.
Felt like beeing in greek. tradional music playing friendly staff an absolutely excellent food 🇬🇷
Great experience
Beautiful meal. Everything was cooked great and the service was amazing too.
Excellent food service, food and atmosphere!

reviews_data.review_text: Lovely evening good food.

Went last night food great, so came back tonight. Very busy, hadn't reserved, but kind, hard working waiter Stretch found us a table. Food, lamb chops and Greek salad were great, service always helpful and friendly. Decided to reserve again!

I was there for my 21st birthday dinner and had a terrible experience. The waitress was extremely unfriendly and unprofessional. She got one of my friend's order wrong, and when she asked for the correct side, the waiter responded with an attitude and even rolled her eyes. We brought this up with another staff member, hoping they’d handle it, but they were argumentative instead of addressing the waitress’s poor behavior.

The french fries were burnt, the lamb chops were over salted. The waiter added his own tip amount of choice of R70 and stated its the 10% of the bill we totalled. When we were done the supervisor sent my wife a whatsapp text apparently thanking her for coming to mykonos but why not use an email or sms to thank customers??
reviews_data.owner_answer:
sorry about your experience, please can you confirm your waitor and phone number from which they texted your wife. I would like to look into this matter
Regards Dimitri
Owner

reviews_data.review_text:
Decent Greek food,
Only lack to experience their typical Greek nights at Mykonos Taverna!
The tzatziki was good, shame I couldn’t say the same for the saganaki.

Last Saturday of the month, plate smashing, was awesome, excellent atmosphere, good food.
Perfect night out
Everything we tasted was amazing. Service was incredible and we got to enjoy an authentic Greek experience... Breaking of plates included

Mykonos Restaurant truly feels like Greece in Cape Town. The cozy, inviting ambiance gives you the vibe of a Greek island escape, while the menu is filled with authentic Mediterranean delights. We tried the grilled chicken, chicken souvlaki, beef skewers, and chicken shawarma - every dish was fresh, full of flavor, and served surprisingly quickly. The staff were outstanding, going above and beyond to make the experience memorable. With top-class food, warm service, and that true Greek charm, this place is a gem not to be missed.

Had a quick lunch between 2 appointments. Nice setting. Friendly staff. Menu was good and easy to navigate. We know Greek/Turkish food so we love their meals. Waiter also gave us more info about the Sea Point CBD. Will visit again.

We ate there last night and got huge value for money! Food is generous and hearty and authentically Greek! Service was attentive. We loved it. It's not a fancy restaurant, but well worth it for Greek cuisine.

I was not 100% happy. We had a Wikideals coupon. I got the idea that, because we already paid, we were forced to accept that in each course something was not available. E.g. the beef strips was not available as well as the cheese cake. And they did not have Graptisers, but later on found one in the fridge. We chose this reataurant to celebrate my sister's 60th birthday. Was a bit dissapointing.
Amazing food

I absolutely cannot fault this place, its just divine!

My israeli friend who i met while travelling a few years ago made me a dish called hummus and since then, ive ordered it at every restaurant that has it on the menu. Cant get enough!

Lovely family orientated atmosphere but great service.

Excellent Halloumi and chicken salad followed by equally excellent baklava cheesecake..a MUST!! superb meal and perfect service from Stretch. Do not miss this restaurant on the Seapoint strip. Could ho straight back for supper to try another dish and repeat baklava cheesecake. Generous portions, we shared both dishes.
A really lovely spot. The best sunshine and service. Lamb chops were divine

Was there on sat night, they def need a waiter or host that is fixed by the door. There were 2 Melissa table bday reservations and half of our table were mixed with the wrong Melissa’s guests then had to get up after ordering. I placed my order at 7pm, we had friends who came at 8 to join us they placed there order but received their food before us. When they were done eating and left we only received our order and our food was cold! Waiter never communicated that due to load shedding our order won’t have chips keep in mind we ordered at 7pm our food with chips and load shedding was from 8. I requested to speak to the manager but was completely disregarded. Worst experience ever
We went to the Greek evening, what a festive place, loved it!

Arrogant and rude management. Booked a table and it was given away because we were 5 minutes late. No phone call, nothing. The manager said "we have a business to run". Clearly don't need our business. We went to Mythos instead. Same Greek food, cheaper prices, and service with a smile.

Food was very decent but service is not the greatest and I'd assume that's because of the colour of my skin. We'd have to ask repeatedly before receiving anything, however we had 1 kind waiter who helped us towards the end.
Atmosphere is good, but lights kept going off.
Wouldn't recommend for a sit it, maybe a takeaway because the ribs are extra yummy

In response to the owners comment:
Maybe take this comment as an opportunity to assess how your staff members may be potentially treating your clients. This is what I experienced with your staff and I was far more disappointed because as a BLACK Zimbabwean woman, I wasn't expecting to be treated that way by your BLACK ZIMBABWEAN workers. As I have made clear, you have 1 waiter with dreadlocks, very kind guy. You have 2 others who are potential problems.
No one insulted you or your business, I stated the facts of my experience.
Whether you take my opinion or not, I'm free to post my review! That's why this section is made available!

Thank you for the prompt response
Best regards
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hi Kimberley ,
Thank you for your feedback however if find your review very insulting.
I don’t usually comment on reviews but this one hit a nerve.
If you didn’t notice100% my staff have the same “skin colour” as you so why should they show any animosity towards you?
I think it’s a disgrace and sad that in today’s society that skin colour is an issue for you especially when you are  receiving great value.
If you have an issue with service just mention it and bring it to our attention and will rectify it as best as we can.
With regards to the lights, yes we do have a problem with our electricity and we are busy sorting it out .
Have a great day and thank you for your support

reviews_data.review_text: Good
A tasty taste of Greece. Well done. What a find.

We recently hosted my Mom’s 70th birthday at Mykonos Taverna Sea Point, and it was absolutely exceptional from start to finish. The food was nothing short of outstanding—authentic, flavorful, and beautifully presented. Every guest raved about their meal.

The service was top-tier: warm, attentive, and genuinely hospitable. The staff went above and beyond to make the celebration special, and we felt so well taken care of throughout the evening.

The ambiance was another highlight. With its cozy yet vibrant  atmosphere, the space struck the perfect balance between festive and intimate—ideal for a milestone birthday. The Staff also arranged for a smashing of a birthday plates with was awesome!!!

Thank you to the entire Mykonos team for helping us create such a memorable evening. Highly recommended for both special occasions and everyday dining!
Great food, the service was fast and the vibe was right ✅ 👌

The service was fabulous. From the moment we walked in, everything flowed smoothly and we were seated right away with no wait at all. We started with the mezze platter, ordering the small size, but it was anything but small. It came out beautifully arranged, packed with variety, and offered incredible value for the price.

We also tried the seafood trio, which was very good. The ingredients tasted fresh and thoughtfully prepared. The shrimp were a little overcooked and the fish was swimming in butter, but the flavors still came together in a way that made us smile. It felt like a high five for our taste buds.

We were genuinely impressed by the portion sizes and how affordable everything was. The ambiance added to the charm. It was playful, welcoming, and full of personality. The whole experience made us want to come back again soon
Phenomenal! Chicken Gyro and Spanakopita. It was lovely. Very friendlu staff. Highly recommended

Seems the bar team added their own ingredients to a simple G&T. One other person tasted it and it tasted strange. Left me dizzy in the first  10 - 15 minutes and had to leave. As women we aren't safe anywhere. Wouldn't recommend for females.
Love the new setup. Bravo Demetri and the food as always is phenomenal and the service. See you soon Malaka
Food was okay. Nothing special. Better Greek food out there. Service was great though! Super cold in the restaurant too which wasn’t very comfortable.

This Greek restaurant's food was excellent, and its servers friendly, but several things left you feeling a tad disappointed. We went in the evening, and as nice as the ambience is, tiny candles on the tables is not enough light in a restaurant. We could barely see the menus in front of our noses. In addition, the servers were hard to understand, rushed (they took my plate away when I was about halfway through my meal), and didn't check up on us nearly often enough to be practical.
Nice Greek restuarant in Sea Point. lovely decor. Staff was very friendly. The food was not too bad.
Really enjoyed my sister’s birthday today. Shout out to Shutman and Stretch for making my sister’s birthday special. Good service, good vibes and we promise to come back anytime soon 💯🙏

This place was definitely amazing. We went there for the first time with a wiki deal and the service was impeccable.  The food was delicious.  Everything about this place just gave "come again". Will definitely be visiting again.
The Manager has gave us the best customer service.
it's was magical

review_questions.Group size: 2 people, Suitable for all group sizes

reviews_data.review_text: Frequently visit Mykonos and love their Gyros. This time, we Uber Eats them and got served the worst quality lamb- half of it was inedible. Probably won’t be back and will definitely not recommend to anyone.

New venue, we were excited!
Booked outside, got seated inside next to the reception desk, complained and then moved
Slow confused service staff, front of house gentleman was great
Starters great, but my main order lamb chops were fatty and waiver thin. You can't ask for medium rear, medium because these chops are too thin to show any grilling skills with.
Rest of the meal was okay and enjoyable.
PS. Didn't see or got offered a kiddies menu...
New venue has the sun in your eyes problem and imagine will be boiling in coming summer.
Good luck to the Mykonos team in your 3rd venue for a Sea point favourite
reviews_data.owner_answer:
thanks for your constructive feedback, noted and relook going forward.
Thank you for support

reviews_data.review_text: shocking experience, the restaurant was under staffed and the food took almost 2 hours to arrive. When it arrived it was cold, and arrived at different times, the amount we paid for the quality of food was horrendous. It was an awful experience. Sadly I will not be returning.

Review for Mykonos Taverna, Seapoint

Had a lovely experience at Mykonos in seapoint! The setting was beautiful, and the atmosphere had that perfect relaxed island vibe. I was especially impressed with the pricing—surprisingly affordable for the quality and location, which made the meal feel like great value.

The service was warm and attentive without being overbearing. Staff were friendly and made us feel welcome throughout.

The only downside for me was the chips. They were hand-cut, which I usually love, but unfortunately they came out a bit too over-fried, leaving them overly crispy and a little hard to enjoy, their lamb chops were a bit bland however when it came to the grilled chicken there was definitely nothing they could have done better, it was devine. It’s a small thing in the bigger picture, but definitely something that could be improved.

Overall, I’d still absolutely recommend Mykonos Tavern. A great spot to enjoy a meal with good service and fair pricing in a stunning location!
Great meal and service!

Long established Sea Point eaterie.
Standard, non fussy good quality Greek style food.
Large portion of tasty Kleftiko and and silky mash potato.
Fish combo could have been hotter when served, just on the edge of it being sent back.
Will, of course go back.

One dish, youvesti, was really good. The other dish, moussaka, was burned on one corner and was okay. The waiter never checked on us after our order was taken and our food was served to us by another waitress. Come time to pay the check and the waiter, who sat us and took our ordered, tried twice for us to leave a tip once before running the credit card and then after running the credit card. No real service, but that was the only point and time that he tried to go above a beyond. Really disappointed after that. Especially after being here for 2 weeks and knowing that tipping is not typical. I wouldn't come back here. Go a few doors down to Posticino Italian Restaurant; the food and service there is AMAZING. You won't be disappointed like we were tonight by Mykonos meal.
Really great setting, great atmosphere, friendly service, and awesome food. I just had the Mousakka, with rice & salad. It was very good.

New building is so awkwardly small. Must say that the food, service and atmosphere at Mykonos Claremont is simply faar superior. How on earth can the experience between two branches feel so different? Meal and service was okay, nothing to get excited about.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hi Adrian
We are not affiliated to Claremont but thank you for your feedback

reviews_data.review_text: Loved their food. To be honest, the CBC Amber Weiss made the food even more tasty. We ordered a meat platter for four and... the portioning was phenomenal. The only tad disappointment was the Baklava, it was way too sweet... felt like it missed something. Nevertheless, will go again!!!

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Calamari, Hummus, The Mykonos Mezze Platter

reviews_data.review_text: Delicious food with excellent service.

Authentic Greek food, served by a mix of local and Greek descendant South Africans. In one of Cape Town’s most lively and touristic area. It’s a definite must try for anyone wanting a taste of the Mediterranean.

PS; they have also just renovated, giving it a beautiful modern aesthetic to match the atmosphere.

Well done Dimitri and team 👏🏽👌🏽
Loved the food! Affordable and various Greek dishes! Lovely restaurant.

Fourth time at Mykonos Tavern. Always busy and viby. The food is fantastic. Counting the days until our next visit.
For my wife and I, a vacation to Seapoint is not complete without a visit to Mykonos Taverna for dinner. The Mezze is always a favourite of ours.

review_questions.Recommended dishes: The Mykonos Mezze Platter, Lamb Shank

reviews_data.review_text: Had a great dinner tonight. Got the mezze plate to share for 2 people. Service was 100%, loved our server. Fun restaurant too.
It's so appreciated

Food is ok not crazy but ok. I understand that we are not in Greece though so cannot be too severe.

The issue is more the service time which is quite slow.

Took some wine as well which is good.

To be noted that the personnel is very kind which is much appreciated.

Excellent decor and layout. Very good service. Ribs were very tasty and fell off the bone, lamb chops were solid but you may as well do a braai if you want chops. Side salad and pita were small but tasty. Monday special is worth going for.

Do not order the mash. Easily the worst mash I have ever eaten. One of the only things I've sent back in Cape Town.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hi
Thanks for feedback but Mykonos Sea Point is not affiliated to Mykonos Claremont.
Please be informed that this review is under Mykonos Sea Point.
This review is for Claremont as Mykonos Sea Point is currently closed due to relocation

reviews_data.review_text: Such a great spot in the Mother City giving one a taste of Greece. They open at 5:30pm so be sure to book a table as it gets crazy busy. Food is really delicious and staff are friendly. Prices are reasonable with an average of R80 for a main.

Mykonos Taverna might look like nothing special from the outside but don't let the looks fool it, it's an amazing restaurant that provides great speedy service, awesome food, variety and good portions.
Also they have a special on the last Saturday of the month where you get authentic Greek food, Greek dancers and you can break some plates.
Great place for supper, family events and etc.
Loses one star because it feels that you are sometimes forgotten about after you order drinks and food.

A Gem found in the heart of Sea Point. It was the perfect Greek experience, the laid back atmosphere makes way to easy conversations at the table. The food was authentic and prepared to perfection. I opted for the Grilled Kingklip and salad. The decor inside and out is amazing and extremely welcoming. It has become one of my favourites

Genuinely one of the worst meals I have ever had. Coming from the UK we love South Africa for its incredible food. We decided to stay in one night and got a delivery from here as we have a 4 month old. What a mistake. It turned up after 1.5 hours and was missing half the order and was cold. We then complained and they re did the order. Again 1.5 hours later it turns up cold and missing parts of the order. The salad was full of water and the gyros was dry. Avoid at all costs. Also, that’s a Naan, not a pitta. All is all horrific.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Then go back to the UK and eat at home,

reviews_data.review_text: Great Greek food, at reasonable prices. Highly recommended.
Excellent Greek cuisine, good prices, great service!

reviews_data.review_text:
Mykonos in Seapoint is an absolute gem! From the moment you walk in, you’re welcomed with warmth and genuine hospitality that makes you feel right at home. The staff are fantastic — attentive, friendly, and passionate about ensuring a wonderful dining experience.

The food? Simply outstanding! The tzatziki was perfectly creamy, the chicken tender and grilled to perfection, and the t-bone was the best I’ve ever tasted. The portions are generous, and everything is made with fresh, high-quality ingredients.

Comida muito saborosa e bem servida.
Recomendo, ambiente agradável e atendimento atencioso.
Besser an die Waterfront...
Had a table of 16, so between all we had a bit of everything, not 1 complaint on the food or service, we'll done guys keep it up, if we stayed closer we would definitely visit more

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Moussaka, Chicken and Chips, Kebab, Chicken Skewers

reviews_data.review_text: I’ve been here before and I don’t remember it to be as good as it was this time. It was one of the best meals I have had in a long time. The lamb yiro is amazing. We shared a few dishes and all of them were really really good. I heard that they may be closing and or moving some time soon. I hope they move and don’t close down because this is a really top Greek restaurant in Sea Point. Phone and book because it is popular and gets very busy.
Lovely place! Good food and atmosphere
